---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is OB a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (4 Points)"
  description="OB is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 4 points (O=1, B=3), OB is an objection. A useful B-dump in international Scrabble play."
  keywords="is ob a scrabble word, ob scrabble valid, ob sowpods only, ob objection scrabble, ob 4 points scrabble, two letter b words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is OB a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (4 Points)",
    "description": "OB is valid in SOWPODS (Collins) but NOT in TWL. Worth 4 points, OB is an objection — useful for B-tile management in international play.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ob-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is OB a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OB is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List) used in North American play. It scores 4 points (O=1, B=3)." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does OB mean?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OB is a noun meaning an objection. It's a British informal shortening — 'No obs' meaning 'no objections.' Collins accepted it as a legitimate word reflecting informal British English usage." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What two-letter B words are valid in both dictionaries?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS: BA (5pts), BE (4pts), BI (4pts), BO (4pts), BY (7pts), AB (4pts). OB is SOWPODS-only. The B tile is worth 3 points, so all B-words score at least 4 points." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is OB a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">OB — a shortened form of "objection" — is one of those SOWPODS-exclusive words that gives international players an extra B-dump option. At 4 points, it's not flashy, but it's tactically useful when you need to shed a B tile in Collins games. North American players beware: OB is completely invalid in TWL.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-950/30 to-amber-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-orange-500/70">⚠ SOWPODS Only</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OB</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-orange-300 font-semibold mb-3">4 points · O(1) + B(3) · An objection · SOWPODS only</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">OB is valid in Collins (international) but INVALID in TWL (North America). A useful B-tile outlet in SOWPODS games, especially when BO or BA don't fit the board position.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/30 bg-orange-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">✗</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Invalid TWL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">✓</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-400">2 B-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Does OB Mean?</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Definition</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">OB is a <span class="text-white font-medium">noun meaning an objection</span>. It's a British informal shortening — "No obs" meaning "no objections." Collins includes many informal shortenings that TWL considers too casual for competitive play.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">All Two-Letter B Words</h2>
      <p>B is a solid 3-point tile with several two-letter options. OB adds one more for SOWPODS players:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BI</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AB</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts ✓</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-orange-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OB</span><span class="text-orange-400 text-xs">4pts SOWPODS</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">OB vs BO: Mirror Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-500/30 bg-orange-950/10"><p class="text-orange-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">OB — SOWPODS Only</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">O(1) + B(3) = 4pts. An objection. Only playable in Collins games. Use when BO doesn't fit the board layout.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">BO — Both Dictionaries</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B(3) + O(1) = 4pts. A type of fig tree (short for bodhi). Safe in any Scrabble game. Same score, different direction.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Play OB</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Board position matters:</span> When BO doesn't fit (B needs to go second), OB gives you the reverse option in SOWPODS games. Same 4 points, different letter order.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Cross-word creation:</span> O is incredibly common on boards (8 tiles in the bag). Playing B adjacent to an existing O to form OB while your main word scores separately is a common tactic.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Endgame flexibility:</span> Having OB as an additional B-word (beyond BO, BA, BE, BI, BY, AB) gives SOWPODS players more options for their final plays in tight board positions.</p></div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-bo-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is BO a Scrabble Word? The Mirror of OB</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-od-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is OD a Scrabble Word? Another O- Two-Letter Word</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word's validity instantly — free, realtime, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
